Time Model Statistics

  • DB Time represents total time in user calls
  • DB CPU represents CPU time of foreground processes
  • Total CPU Time represents foreground and background processes
  • Statistics including the word "background" measure background process time, therefore do not contribute to the DB time statistic
  • Ordered by % of DB time in descending order, followed by Statistic Name

01nsu704npuwh INSERT INTO TEMPT_DAILYINVOICE ( INVOICENUMBER, PDATE, RETAILERID, RETAILERNAME, ITEMNAME, UNITQTY, NETSALEVALUE, DISTRIBUTORUID, EMPLOYEEUID, DISTRIBUTOR, DSR, DSR_NUMBER, OPERATIONALDISTRICT ) SELECT IX.ID AS INVOICENUMBER , IX.PDATE , CASE WHEN NVL(O.TLRNUMBER, 0) = 0 THEN TO_CHAR(O.ID) ELSE TO_CHAR(O.TLRNUMBER) END AS RETAILERID , O.NAME AS RETAILERNAME , T.DESCRIPTION AS ITEMNAME , SUM(IX.UNITQTY) AS UNITQTY , SUM(IX.NETSALEVALUE) AS NETSALEVALUE , D.PUID AS DISTRIBUTORUID , E.PUID AS EMPLOYEEUID , D.NAME AS DISTRIBUTOR , E.FIRSTNAME || ' ' || CASE WHEN E.LASTNAME = '.' THEN '' ELSE TO_CHAR(NVL(E.LASTNAME, '')) END AS DSR , A.TLSNUMBER AS DSR_NUMBER , AR.DESCRIPTION AS OPERATIONALDISTRICT FROM ( SELECT I.ID, I.PDATE, I.DISTRIBUTORUID, I.AGENTUID, I.OUTLETUID, IL.ITEMUID, I.SUBMITTEDDATE, I.MPT_SALESMODELENUM, I.EXPIRYDATE, I.MPT_TYPEENUM, IL.UNITQTY, IL.NETSALEVALUE, CASE WHEN I.MPT_TYPEENUM = 30 THEN 1 ELSE ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY I.MPT_TYPEENUM, IL.ITEMUID , IL.ITEMBATCHID, IL.SERIALNUMBER, IL.SERIALNUMBER2 ORDER BY I.PDATE) END INV_NUM FROM TXNINVOICE I INNER JOIN TXNINVOICELINE IL ON I.PUID = IL.TXNINVOICEUID AND I.SITEUID = IL.TXNINVOICE_SITEUID AND IL.MPT_TYPEENUM = 1 AND (I.PDATE>= :B2 AND I.PDATE <= :B1 ) AND (I.SUBMITTEDDATE IS NOT NULL OR I.MPT_SALESMODELENUM = 2) AND I.EXPIRYDATE IS NULL AND IL.EXPIRYDATE IS NULL ) IX INNER JOIN OUTLET O ON IX.OUTLETUID = O.PUID AND IX.INV_NUM = 1 INNER JOIN ITEM T ON IX.ITEMUID = T.PUID INNER JOIN DISTRIBUTOR D ON IX.DISTRIBUTORUID = D.PUID INNER JOIN AGENT A ON IX.AGENTUID = A.PUID INNER JOIN EMPLOYEE E ON A.EMPLOYEEUID = E.PUID INNER JOIN AREA AR ON D.BUSINESSAREAUID = AR.PUID WHERE (IX.PDATE >= :B2 AND IX.PDATE <= :B1 ) AND (IX.MPT_TYPEENUM = :B7 ) AND (:B6 IS NULL OR IX.DISTRIBUTORUID = :B6 ) AND (:B5 IS NULL OR IX.AGENTUID = :B5 ) AND (:B4 = 0 OR D.PUID IN (SELECT PUID FROM DISTRIBUTORUIDS_DAILYINVOICE)) AND (NVL(O.ISFREELANCEAGENT, 0) <> 1) AND (:B3 IS NULL OR D.MPT_CHAN NELUID = :B3 ) GROUP BY IX.ID , IX.PDATE , O.ID , O.NAME , T.DESCRIPTION , D.PUID , E.PUID , D.NAME , E.FIRSTNAME , E.LASTNAME , A.TLSNUMBER , AR.DESCRIPTION , O.TLRNUMBER ORDER BY D.NAME

45ra532ktzz6r INSERT INTO TEMPPAYMENT SELECT T.PUID, (NVL(COB.BFBALNCE, 0)) AS BF, T.AMOUNT, T.CLAWBACK, T.PANELTY, (NVL(COB.BFBALNCE, 0)) + AMOUNT - CLAWBACK - PANELTY AS PAYINGAMOUNT FROM ( SELECT KK.PUID , SUM(KK.AMOUNT) AS AMOUNT , SUM(KK.CLAWBACK) AS CLAWBACK , SUM(KK.PANELTY) AS PANELTY FROM ( SELECT O.PUID, SUM(CASE WHEN C.MPT_COMMISSIONTYPE = 1 AND CPO.ISELIGIBLE = 1 THEN NVL(CPO.AMOUNT, 0) ELSE 0 END) AS AMOUNT, SUM(CASE WHEN C.MPT_COMMISSIONTYPE = 4 AND CPO.ISELIGIBLE = 1 THEN NVL(CPO.AMOUNT, 0) ELSE 0 END) AS CLAWBACK, SUM(NVL(CPO.PENALTYAMOUNT, 0)) AS PANELTY FROM CM_PRO_HIS_DETAILS CPHD INNER JOIN CM_PAYMENTOUTLET CPO ON CPHD.PROCESSID = CPO.PROCESSID AND CPO.COMMISIONUID = CPHD.COMMISIONUID INNER JOIN SIM S ON CPO.SIMNUMBER = S.SIMNUMBER INNER JOIN OUTLET O ON CPO.OUTLETUID = O.PUID INNER JOIN COMMISION C ON CPO.COMMISIONUID = C.PUID INNER JOIN TEMPPAYMENT_RETCMPAYAUTO T ON CPHD.TRANSID = T.TRID WHERE CPO.ISELIGIBLE = 1 AND CPHD.COMMISIONUID = :B1 GROUP BY O.PUID UNION ALL SELE CT O.PUID, 0 AS AMOUNT, 0 AS CLAWBACK, SUM(NVL(CPO.PENALTYAMOUNT, 0)) AS PANELTY FROM CM_PRO_HIS_DETAILS CPHD INNER JOIN CM_PAYMENTOUTLET CPO ON CPHD.PROCESSID = CPO.PROCESSID AND CPO.COMMISIONUID = CPHD.COMMISIONUID INNER JOIN SIM S ON CPO.SIMNUMBER = S.SIMNUMBER INNER JOIN OUTLET O ON CPO.OUTLETUID = O.PUID INNER JOIN COMMISION C ON CPO.COMMISIONUID = C.PUID INNER JOIN TEMPPAYMENT_RETCMPAYAUTO T ON CPHD.TRANSID = T.TRID WHERE CPO.ISELIGIBLE = 0 AND CPHD.COMMISIONUID = :B1 AND NVL(CPO.PENALTYAMOUNT, 0) > 0 GROUP BY O.PUID )KK GROUP BY KK.PUID ) T LEFT OUTER JOIN COMMISIONOUTLETBALANCE COB ON T.PUID = COB.OUTLETUID

          Findings and Recommendations
          ----------------------------

Finding 1: I/O Throughput
Impact is 5.87 active sessions, 42.53% of total activity.
---------------------------------------------------------
The throughput of the I/O subsystem was significantly lower than expected.

   Recommendation 1: Host Configuration
   Estimated benefit is 5.87 active sessions, 42.53% of total activity.
   --------------------------------------------------------------------
   Action
      Consider increasing the throughput of the I/O subsystem. Oracle's
      recommended solution is to stripe all data files using the SAME
      methodology. You might also need to increase the number of disks for
      better performance.
   Rationale
      During the analysis period, the average data files' I/O throughput was
      56 M per second for reads and 2.7 M per second for writes. The average
      response time for single block reads was 17 milliseconds.

   Recommendation 2: Host Configuration
   Estimated benefit is 3.49 active sessions, 25.28% of total activity.
   --------------------------------------------------------------------
   Action
      The performance of some data and temp files was significantly worse than
      others. If striping all files using the SAME methodology is not
      possible, consider striping these file over multiple disks.

   Recommendation 1: Application Analysis
   Estimated benefit is .62 active sessions, 4.47% of total activity.
   ------------------------------------------------------------------
   Action
      Investigate application logic for possible reduction of connect and
      disconnect calls. For example, you might use a connection pool scheme in
      the middle tier.


Finding 6: Undersized Redo Log Buffer
Impact is .31 active sessions, 2.25% of total activity.
-------------------------------------------------------
Waits for redo log buffer space were consuming significant database time.

   Recommendation 1: Host Configuration
   Estimated benefit is .31 active sessions, 2.25% of total activity.
   ------------------------------------------------------------------
   Action
      Investigate the possibility of improving the performance of I/O to the
      online redo log files.
   Rationale
      The average size of writes to the online redo log files was 981 K and
      the average time per write was 150 milliseconds.

   Symptoms That Led to the Finding:
   ---------------------------------
      Wait class "Configuration" was consuming significant database time.
      Impact is .34 active sessions, 2.43% of total activity.

Wait class "Concurrency" was not consuming significant database time.
